3. **Handle Errors/Warnings:** Look at the validation section first. If any warning (WARN) or failure (FAIL) is reported, explicitly call out how it affects the reliability of the measurements.
4. **No Speculation:** If the data does not support a confident conclusion or lacks certain counter groups, state that clearly instead of guessing.

